HEADWORD: Shippon
<hw>Ship"pon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A cowhouse; a
shippen.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Bessy would either do fieldwork, or attend to the cows, the
<qex>shippon</qex>, or churn, or make cheese.</q>
<rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ship railway</ent>⟦br⟧
